    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180\u00b0C/ 160\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 4</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Roughly chop your<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-cheesy-lean-pork-bolognese-bake/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>lean</strong> <strong>pork</strong> <strong>mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) with the <strong>chopped chestnut mushrooms</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then cook for 5-6 min or until the mince is starting to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-cheesy-lean-pork-bolognese-bake/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> in 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-cheesy-lean-pork-bolognese-bake/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince has started to brown, add the <strong>diced tomato[es]</strong>, your<strong> tomato paste</strong> and <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min further, giving everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>bolognese sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-cheesy-lean-pork-bolognese-bake/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tortiglioni pasta </strong>and <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Pour the <strong>bolognese sauce</strong> and <strong>beef stock</strong> over and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Tip: Try to make sure that most of the pasta is submerged in the liquid</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-cheesy-lean-pork-bolognese-bake/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cover the dish with <strong>tin foil</strong>,<strong> </strong>put it in the oven and cook for 20 min, then remove it from the oven and mix everything together</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if it's looking a little dry</p><p>Return the dish to the oven for 20 min further or until the pasta is cooked, the sauce resembles a rag\u00f9-like consistency and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-cheesy-lean-pork-bolognese-bake/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Once the pasta is cooked, increase the oven temperature to 220\u00baC/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Remove the dish from the oven and discard the tin foil</p><p>Top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and return the dish to the oven for a further 5 min, or until the cheese is golden brown \u2013 this is your<strong> cheesy lean pork bolognese bake</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-cheesy-lean-pork-bolognese-bake/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cheesy</strong> <strong>lean pork bolognese bake </strong>with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
